{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Plan-review remediation ‚Äî final targeted round on the S2/S4/S5 residual (the inconsistencies the (b) edits introduced). Applied:\n\n- **S2 (0ee8):** dropped the stale \"`autolander-bot` vote ACL / bot-only ACL\" cross-ref. S1 grants the `Autosubmit` vote to group **Contributors (requesters)** so *agents* set the label via S4's `land`; the loop itself casts no votes. Re-worded the S1 dependency to \"requester-votable (Contributor) ACL\" and clarified the loop only *selects on* `label:Autosubmit+1`.\n- **REST-submittable vs FFO-landable (S2 + S4):** added an explicit definition ‚Äî *REST-submittable* = `submittable=True` (gate votes MAX); *FFO-landable* = also on `main`'s current tip. Under FFO (ADR-0040) they diverge (a behind-tip change stays `submittable=True` but `POST /submit` fails `not fast-forward`). Corrected S2's TOCTOU guard to re-check **FFO-landable** (tip-parent), not just `is:submittable`; framed S4's `needs_rebase` as \"REST-submittable but not FFO-landable.\"\n- **S4‚ÜíS5 heartbeat dependency (S4 + S5):** S4 read the heartbeat \"(from S5)\" without declaring it. Added an explicit **interface dependency on S5** in S4's Dependencies ‚Äî a heartbeat-*contract* dependency (agreed location + staleness threshold), NOT a build-order blocker. Tightened S5 AC5 to name that heartbeat as the interface contract S4's `lander_down` reads.\n- **Bogus CONTRIBUTING ¬ßFFO citation (S4):** there is no \"¬ßFFO\" section. Repointed the `lander_down` message to **CONTRIBUTING ¬ß2e (\"Submit\"), ADR-0040** ‚Äî the actual home of the manual FFO rebase-and-submit steps.\n- **S4‚ÜíADR-0042 downstream forward-reference:** removed. ADR-0042 is authored downstream by S6; S4 no longer cites a doc that does not yet exist. `land --help` now cites only `docs/land-contract.md`; the ADR‚Üîcontract linkage stays in S6.\n- **S5 existing-file edit targets (3c55):** added a `## Files` section (new vs edited) and expanded `file_impact` to the full set ‚Äî new: `Dockerfile.autolander`, `monitoring_autolander.tf`; edited existing: `docker-compose.yml`, `terraform/ssm.tf`, `scripts/fetch-secrets.sh`, `scripts/observability.sh`. Noted `iam.tf` as read-only (already grants the SSM prefix) and the `All-Projects refs/meta/config` capability grant as an operator cutover, not a repo file.\n\n**Declined (over-specification):** did NOT pin an exact heartbeat staleness threshold (seconds) / poll interval or fix the AC6 queue-wait histogram bucket boundaries. These are implementer decisions; the plan should carry the *contract* (an agreed location + a staleness threshold, a histogram metric) and let the implementation choose the concrete numbers ‚Äî over-pinning them here reduces flexibility without adding review value. Kept \"a few poll intervals\" / \"bounded\" as written."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783784026487395001,"uuid":"4bd73dcc-c362-4678-8ad0-1603f8f39932"}